All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Animal
Animal class is the abstract super class for all animals on an island.
Bird
Bird class represents a birds on the island.
Direction
Direction Enumeration stores variables for the direction animals can be heading on the island.
Egg
Egg class represents an egg on the island.
Foliage
Foliage class is the abstract super class for plant life on an island.
Grass
Grass class represents grass at a particular point on the island.
Island
Island class represents a two-dimesional world of fixed width and height and the items contained within it.
IslandItem
IslandItem class is the abstract super class for all items on an island.
IslandSimulator
IslandSimulator class controls the creation and simulation of Islands.
Kiwi
Kiwi class represents a kiwi on the island.
LaysEggs
LaysEggs interface allows classes to implement methods to layEggs
LaysInNest
LaysInNest interface extends LaysEggs and allows classes to implement methods to build nests and incubate eggs.
LivingThing
LivingThing class is the abstract super class for all living things on an island.
Main
 
Mammal
Mammal class is the abstract super class for all mammals on an island.
Nest
Nest class represents a nests on the island.
Rabbit
Rabbit class represents rabbits.
